{
  "stem": "21786.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They knew perfectly well where they are going.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they took all 5,000 people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And literally, without missing a night, they gassed them. 22 people were pulled out of transport.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they were the personnel which were nursing personnel, and few doctors, who were pulled out by the chief angel of death called Dr.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Josef Mengele.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Also, about six young boys were brought back, or brought into the-- in that case, into the camp of the-- where the adult males were. 28 people were pulled out by Mengele.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we had an order that we should prepare everybody who is in the hospital compound for transportation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we should prepare them on stretchers for carrying them onto the trucks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They didn't have any stretchers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So from the bunks, we ripped off the-- kind of one plank on each side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we took a blanket, and in front of the blanket, we put four knots on it, and were prepared to put the sick people on it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While we were working with it, it was already early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And suddenly, the door opens into the block.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in walks a slew of SS men, headed with Mengele, and headed with [PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] the head of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I forgot who it was at that point, the head of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think that it was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't know whether it was Herr-- I forgot.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they changed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And anyhow, now, the normal routine was that there was a guard in front of the block who should warn that an SS man, in this case, I mean, the whole SS hierarchy is approaching.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
